        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/df705f/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2023-07-08T16:10:34.304Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Yes! Because otherwise forwards confusingly look like you actually wrote the forwarded text.</p>\n<p>And to respond to your comment about privacy: I think an even better solution that wouldn‚Äôt compromise privacy at all is that it could use the same (or similar) ‚Äúbox‚Äù that Reply uses, but just don‚Äôt have a name in it (like the Reply functionality has). That way it‚Äôs obvious that it‚Äôs a forward (from <em>someone</em>), and that you didn‚Äôt write it. Also, another benefit is that it would have any comments you made on the forward, exactly like with a Reply.</p>",
